<br>
Thurg Gate Potions:<br>
(From EQtraders.com)<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Highest Skill Trivials</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> Pottery: 122-123 <br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Drops to Collect</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> <br>
1 Small Brick of Velium <br>
3 Crystalline Silks <br>
2 Small Pieces of Velium <br>
<!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><span style="text-decoration:underline">Ingredients to Buy from Vendor</span><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> <br>
2 Glass Shards <br>
High Quality Firing Sheet <br>
You say, 'Hail Frundle Frenkler' <br>
You say, 'What are Velium Vapors?' <br>
Frundle Frenkler says, &quot;Ahh, you come seeking my family recipe? After all you've done for our people it's the least I can do. First you must fashion a velium vial, then combine the vial with two small pieces of velium in this jar. That's all there is to it. Please keep the recipe a secret.&quot; <br>
[Receive: Velium Purifier] <br>
<br>
You say, &quot;What is a velium vial?&quot; <br>
Frundle Frenkler says &quot;I'm no potter mind you, but if I remember correctly it's a small brick of velium, three crystalline silks, and two glass shards. Then you'll have to finish up by firing it in a kiln with a high quality firing sheet.&quot; <br>
<!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>You don't have to say the last part, I just left it here because it told how to make it</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://members.monarch.net/stomped/EQGateNecklaceQuests.htm" target="top">PoP Gate Necklaces</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Necklace 1 <br>
Start:  Jimlok Keylifter, Plane of Tranquility <br>
Step 1:  Kill &quot;a festering rat&quot; in PoJ           <br>
Step 2:  Turn in bottle to Jimlok Keylifter           <br>
Step 3:  Turn in map to Tabben Bromal, Plane of Knowledge       <br>
  Note:  Have a free container space         <br>
Step 4:  Gather the following items:           <br>
  Tri-coated Metal Casing, Plane of Innovation (random)    <br>
  Size C Spring, Plane of Innovation (random)    <br>
  Creeping Silk Strand, Plane of Disease (Oozes)    <br>
  Congealed Bile-based Ooze, Plane of Nightmare (Virulent Arachnids)   <br>
Step 5:  Combine the items and hand the new container to Tabben Bromal     <br>
Reward:  Small Clockwork Talisman <br>
Strength, Stamina, Wisdom, Intelligence, All Saves 5 <br>
Mana, Hit Points 25 <br>
5 charges of Gate <br>
 <br>
Necklace 2 <br>
Start:  Tabben Bromal, Plane of Knowledge <br>
Step 1:  Say &quot;I am ready&quot; to Tabben Bromal         <br>
  Note:  Have a free container space         <br>
Step 2:  Gather the following items:           <br>
  Crystalline Carapace, Plane of Valor (Spiders)    <br>
  Strands of Living Chain, Plane of Torment (Spiders)    <br>
  Dense Hammered Casing, PoTA (Random Daiku's)    <br>
  A Fiery Powersource (Tower of Solusek Ro)       <br>
Step 3:  Combine the items and hand the new container and your first necklace to Tabben Brommel <br>
Reward:  Powered Clockwork Talisman <br>
Strength, Stamina, Wisdom, Intelligence, All Saves 10 <br>
Mana, Hit Points 50 <br>
15 charges of Gate <br>
 <br>
Necklace 3 <br>
Start:  Elder Clinka, Plane of Tranquility <br>
Step 1:  Hand Elder Clinka the schematic           <br>
  Note:  Have a free container space         <br>
Step 2:  Gather a shard of elemental matter from each of the elemental plains   <br>
Step 3:  Combine the items in the box and hand it and your second necklace to Elder Clinka <br>
Reward:  The Binden Concerfentia <br>
Strength, Stamina, Wisdom, Intelligence, All Saves 15 <br>
Mana, Hit Points 75 <br>
Unlimited charges of Gate <br>
 <br>
The Gate effect has a 20 second casting time. <br>
 <br>
The Gate effect has a component you must have on you.  It is Quintessence of Knowledge. <br>
Skill:  Alchemy <br>
Trivial:  21 <br>
Components:  Erudition Vine (store bought), Taanan Ginko (store bought) <br>
